Implementation Notes for Cost Estimation (P1.1, P1.2):

WHY:
- Hardcoded costs ($15+$20+$25/deployment) were inaccurate
- No regional pricing variations
- Budget checks used fake data

WHAT WAS IMPLEMENTED:
1. PricingEstimator (internal/spending/pricing.go):
   - AWS Pricing API client with us-east-1 override
   - 24-hour price cache with TTL
   - Regional fallback prices for all major regions
   - EstimateCosts() calculates: Fargate, ALB, NAT GW, CloudWatch

2. planInfra updates:
   - Uses PricingEstimator for cost calculation
   - Detailed cost breakdown in output
   - Includes assumptions and disclaimers
   - Falls back to simplified formula if API fails

3. createInfra updates:
   - Uses CostTracker.GetTotalMonthlySpend() for actual spend
   - Falls back to plan.EstimatedCostMo from local state
   - Logs source of spend calculation

KEY DESIGN DECISIONS:
- Fallback-first: Always have a valid estimate even without AWS access
- Cache: 24h TTL balances accuracy vs API calls
- Regional pricing: Hardcoded fallbacks for 10 major regions
- NAT Gateway: Included in estimates (now standard with private subnets)

COST FORMULA:
- Fargate: (cpu/1024 × vcpu_price + mem/1024 × mem_price) × 730h × count
- ALB: hourly_rate × 730h + (users/3000 × 0.008 × 730h)
- NAT GW: 0.045 × 730h + count × 10GB × 0.045
- CloudWatch: count × 1GB × ($0.50 ingestion + $0.03 storage)

